EU publishes grain intervention changes . The European Union published changes to rules under which intervention agencies accept cereals into public stores . In Friday ' s EU Official Journal , EU regulation 689 / 92 was changed to allow cereals with a maximum moisture content of 15 percent , except for maize and sorghum , into intervention stores . Greece was allowed to accept durum wheat containing 14 percent sub - standard grain . Barley with a specific weight of less than 64 kg / hl will not be penalised . The intervention measures , which were approved earlier by the EU cereals management committee , are backdated to July 1 , 1995 . 
